A contractor on Thursday told a court how former Kasarani MP John Chege was arrested after pocketing a Sh100,000 bribe from him. Abdirahman Abdullah told trial magistrate Lawrence Mugambi of the Milimani Anti-Corruption Court the money was to facilitate CDF payment to him of Sh3,342,716.77 for a completed Baba Dogo Secondary School tuition block.  He informed the court that Chege also demanded another Sh50,000 for CDF committee officials to share as facilitation fee. He reported the matter to the EACC where he was given treated currency of Sh100,000 and a tape recorder to entra the MP. The magistrate directed the rest of the witnesses be summoned to testify on March 8 next year.